Former Orlando Pirates Assistant coach, Rhulani Mokwena has resurfaced at Chippa United following his short stint with the Buccaneers. JOHANNESBURG - Former Orlando Pirates assistant coach, Rhulani Mokwena has resurfaced at Chippa United following his short stint with the Buccaneers. Mokwena recently returned from an overseas trip which saw him visiting some European football clubs for a benchmarking exercise. READ: 'I'm prepared to die for Pirates': Rhulani Mokwena The 33-year old joins the Chilli Boys until the end of the season. He will be joined at United by Michael Loftman.